Limpopo transport MEC Makoma Makhurupetje has urged drivers not to drink and drive. Her comments come after a traffic officer was allegedly hit by a drunk driver. The accident happened in Sekhukhune while the officer was on duty during the course of the long weekend. It is believed that the officer was trying to stop the speeding driver, leading to a high-speed chase by the slain cop’s partner until they caught up with him. “Please don’t drink and drive, we cannot continue to have these unnecessary accidents,”MEC Makhurupetje said. The MEC said that the perpetrators had been arrested and will appear in court. She further went on to sent her condolences to the family of the slain cop. –Afro Worldview